;shows throughout the year, showcasing both established Welsh artists, as well as up and coming young&nbsp;talent. We are also part of the Arts Council of Wales 0% Collectorplan scheme, all to help make investing in art easier to do.Art loving dogs are very much welcome. Open Monday - Saturday 10.30 - 5.00Website: http:\/\/www.lionstreetgallery.co.uk","url":"\/businesses\/3312"}},{"id":"llewelyn___company","lat":52.0745383,"lon":-3.1254271,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Llewelyn & Company","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3533"}},{"id":"mayalls_jewellery","lat":52.0745383,"lon":-3.1254271,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Mayalls Jewellery","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3569"}},{"id":"monica","lat":52.0745383,"lon":-3.1254271,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Monica","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3524"}},{"id":"murder_and_mayhem","lat":52.0748207,"lon":-3.1250403,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Murder and Mayhem","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3543"}},{"id":"number_two","lat":52.0738373,"lon":-3.1272771,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Number Two","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3523"}},{"id":"old_railway_line_nursery","lat":52.029888,"lon":-3.208984,"enhanced":null,"type":"attraction","popup":{"title":"The Old Railway Line Garden Centre","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_5807__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"The Old Railway Line Garden Centre is an award winning, family run, independent Garden Centre, Farm Shop and Restaurant combined, offering the very best gardening, home and outdoor living products alongside delicious, fresh, locally produced food and drink.Awarded 'Best Garden Centre in Wales and the West' in 2012, 2013 and 2014 we pride ourselves on the wide range of quality products stocked alongside our helpful, knowledgeable staff. We aim to always provide a shopping experience to remember and a restaurant that never fails to deliver delicious food.The garden centre is situated in the heart of the picturesque Wye Valley, nestling at the foot of the Black Mountains with outstanding views of the Brecon Beacons and surrounding Radnorshire Hills.","url":"\/businesses\/3291"}},{"id":"old_stables_tea_room","lat":52.074052,"lon":-3.1236202,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Old Stables Tea Room","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3258"}},{"id":"oscar_s","lat":52.0745383,"lon":-3.1254271,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Oscar's ","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3223"}},{"id":"outcast_books","lat":52.075602,"lon":-3.1260813,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Outcast Books","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3537"}},[],{"id":"paddles__pedals","lat":52.0809339,"lon":-3.1316879,"enhanced":true,"type":"activity","popup":{"title":"want to canoe?","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_5947__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"River Wye Canoe Hire\r\nWe warmly invite you to hire a canoe and discover the beauty of the River Wye. The Wye is by far one of the most beautiful rivers in the British Isles and one of the few you can navigate by canoe, without restriction, for well over 100 miles.&nbsp;want to canoe?&nbsp;offer you the chance to embark on a relaxing river adventure from several different points along the way, with an array of different routes to choose from, all with their own unique sights, sounds and smells.\r\nFrom its source at the Welsh mountains at Plynlimon, the water meanders through miles of picturesque countryside and diverse wildlife, passing the bustling market towns of Hay-on-Wye, Ross-on-Wye and Monmouth; the city of Hereford, and the charming, picture-postcard villages of Glasbury, Symonds Yat and Tintern, before joining the River Severn at Chepstow.\r\nAlong your journey, you can expect to see a number of spectacular and fascinating characters in their natural habitats, including kingfishers, herons, cormorants, swans and otters &ndash; all from the prime viewpoint of your canoe.\r\nThis peaceful and ever-changing setting is the ideal place to wile away a few hours, spend a day or even a week. Furthermore, what better way to get a bit of aerobic and cardiovascular exercise than canoeing the Wye? Burning calories has never been so relaxing!","url":"\/businesses\/2796"}},{"id":"pembertons_new_books","lat":52.0745383,"lon":-3.1254271,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Pembertons New Books","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3547"}},{"id":"psm_outdoors","lat":52.0738373,"lon":-3.1272771,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"PSM Outdoors","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3441"}},{"id":"red_indigo","lat":52.0738373,"lon":-3.1272771,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Red Indigo","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3471"}},{"id":"river_cafe","lat":52.0459686,"lon":-3.1962181,"enhanced":true,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"The River Caf\u00e9 at Glasbury","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_1846__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"Great food great riverside views at our restaurant\/cafe.\r\nThe River Cafe is licensed and a great place for couples and groups to meet in an informal setting. In the last month we have had groups of architects, bankers, midwives, canoeists (paddlers are here pretty consistently because of our location!) and large wedding and family groups all getting together to enjoy fresh food cooked daily, a pint of local ale, and some excellent homemade cakes.","url":"\/businesses\/3080"}},{"id":"rogues_gallery","lat":52.075602,"lon":-3.1260813,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Rogues Gallery","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3304"}},{"id":"rohan","lat":52.0738373,"lon":-3.1272771,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Rohan","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3528"}},{"id":"rose_and_crown","lat":52.075602,"lon":-3.1260813,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Rose and Crown","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3183"}},{"id":"rose_s_books","lat":52.075602,"lon":-3.1260813,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Rose's Books","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3538"}},{"id":"sage_femme","lat":52.0739558,"lon":-3.1223922,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Sage Femme","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3526"}},{"id":"satori_design","lat":52.0733107,"lon":-3.1268699,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Satori Design","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3567"}},{"id":"shepherds_ice_cream_parlour","lat":52.0745383,"lon":-3.1254271,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Shepherds  Ice Cream Parlour","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3482"}},{"id":"small_farms","lat":52.075602,"lon":-3.1260813,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Small Farms","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3486"}},{"id":"spirit_of_the_andes","lat":52.0746049,"lon":-3.1259833,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Spirit of The Andes","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3518"}},{"id":"swan_at_hay_hotel_copy","lat":52.0726847,"lon":-3.1284007,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Swan at Hay Hotel","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_2942__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"The Swan at Hay is a privately owned hotel and restaurant in the Marches town of Hay-on-Wye where warm hospitality and good food await you. ","url":"\/businesses\/3497"}},{"id":"swan_at_hay_hotel","lat":52.0726847,"lon":-3.1284007,"enhanced":null,"type":"accommodation","popup":{"title":"Swan at Hay Hotel","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_2941__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"The Swan at Hay is a privately owned hotel and restaurant in the Marches town of Hay-on-Wye where warm hospitality and good food await you. As a former coaching inn, the hotel is full of character, from the original Georgian windows overlooking the garden, to the cobbled stable block to the rear. \r\n\r\nThe bedrooms are full of charm and character, and are all different in shape and size. Some have views of the beautiful garden, while others have period features. All rooms are decorated to the same standard, with en-suite bathrooms and their Gilchrist & Soames toiletries, flatscreen TVs, DVD players and generous tea tray.","url":"\/businesses\/2830"}},{"id":"the_black_hill_gallery","lat":52.0746049,"lon":-3.1259833,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"The Black Hill Gallery","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3556"}},{"id":"the_black_mountains_bindery","lat":52.0735545,"lon":-3.1248771,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"The Black Mountains Bindery","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3545"}},{"id":"the_bookshop","lat":52.0746049,"lon":-3.1259833,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"The Bookshop","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3541"}},{"id":"the_bowie_gallery","lat":52.0741991,"lon":-3.1251705,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"The Bowie Gallery","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3559"}},{"id":"the_children_s_bookshop","lat":52.084954,"lon":-3.1183774,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"The Children's Bookshop","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3555"}},{"id":"the_dolls_house","lat":52.0706349,"lon":-3.1302603,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"The Dolls House","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3562"}},{"id":"the_fudge_shop","lat":52.07246563743,"lon":-3.1283928989502,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"The Fudge Shop","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3481"}},{"id":"the_globe","lat":52.0770228,"lon":-3.1251102,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"The Globe","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3477"}},{"id":"the_granary","lat":52.075602,"lon":-3.1260813,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"The Granary","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3238"}},{"id":"the_great_english_outdoors","lat":52.0738373,"lon":-3.1272771,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"The Great English Outdoors","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3535"}},{"id":"the_green_room","lat":52.0748207,"lon":-3.1250403,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"The Green Room","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3565"}},{"id":"the_hay_makers","lat":52.0745462,"lon":-3.1245956,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"The Hay Makers","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3561"}},{"id":"the_old_barn_inn","lat":52.032504108665,"lon":-3.2065053227539,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"The Old Barn Inn","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3178"}},{"id":"the_poetry_bookshop","lat":52.0754646,"lon":-3.1244581999999,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"The Poetry Bookshop","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3544"}},{"id":"three_horseshoes","lat":52.0222395,"lon":-3.1892596,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"The Three Horseshoes","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3235"}},{"id":"three_cocks_hotel","lat":52.0323985,"lon":-3.2061619999999,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Three Cocks Hotel","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3244"}},{"id":"three_tuns","lat":52.075602,"lon":-3.1260813,"enhanced":null,"type":"food","popup":{"title":"Three Tuns","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3473"}},{"id":"cadarn_tregoyd_mountain_riders","lat":52.0313113,"lon":-3.1704336,"enhanced":true,"type":"activity","popup":{"title":"Tregoyd Mountain Riders","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3627"}},{"id":"vintage_mercantile","lat":52.0735552,"lon":-3.1266864,"enhanced":null,"type":"retail","popup":{"title":"Vintage Mercantile","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/3525"}},{"id":"westview_guesthouse","lat":52.0680844,"lon":-3.1830662,"enhanced":true,"type":"accommodation","popup":{"title":"Westview Guesthouse","image":"\/website\/var\/tmp\/thumb_1783__business_listing_thumb.jpeg","text":"Westview Guesthouse with a welcome to delight and every window frames a picture of mountains and valleys. A heap of magazines to flick through. A cup of tea to soothe and a wedge of home made cake to accompany. A red kite lazily drifts on the thermals, a tractor rumbles past and times drifts by. Your bedroom with a shower that produces bountiful hot water, a floor that toasts your toes in winter and windows with views over hills and woods. A sumptious mattress to ease your bones, home made biscuits to dunk in your tea. Filtered fresh air without opening a window and wi-fi connections to keep up with your other life.\r\nOur food is our passion - breakfast is home made bread smothered in lemon curd made from Malcolm's eggs. More eggs, but scrambled and topped with smoked salmon from Black Mountain Smokery. Sausages hand made by Sue on her farm down the road, from rare breed organic pork with thick bacon slices from Martin and Kate at Glaiser Farm. Try the special of the day - maybe parmesan and sundried tomato Welsh cakes or potato blinis. Vegetarians have their own menu including spicy lentil burgers and laver bread patties. An option for dinner is the River Cafe at Glasbury for a friendly welcome and a menu to delight. On a summer evening sit on the deck, watch the river drift by and wait for the spectacular dark skies of the Brecon Beacons to enchant.\r\nWhilst you're here - amble into Hay-on-Wye to explore the town of books, Booths a particular joy with a cafe to linger in for coffee and buns. Not books alone, delectable clothes shops and curious antiques to distract and delight. More demanding hiking will reveal miles of peaks and ridges, plunging scarps and views to remember forever or just savour a gentle walk around&nbsp;the local woods teeming with wildlife. Borrow our electric Twizy to challenge your senses with the wind in your hair and the lambs to spy and a tick for your eco credentials.To book online please click through to our website.","url":"\/businesses\/2863"}},{"id":"will_lewis_photography","lat":52.043505,"lon":-3.1944463,"enhanced":null,"popup":{"title":"Will Lewis Photography","image":"","text":"","url":"\/businesses\/2865"}},{"id":"wye_valley_canoes__river_caf","lat":52.0459686,"lon":-3.1962181,"enhanced":true,"type":"activity","popup":{"title":"Wye Valley Canoes","image":"","text":"Wye Valley Canoes, Bikes and Beds sits on the banks of the River Wye four miles west of Hay-on-Wye. We are located on the bridge at Glasbury and have a fleet of Canadian canoes, single kayaks and double kayaks as well as Mountain bikes and Vespa's. You can paddle or pedal for a few hours or a few days. You start with us at the Wye Valley Canoe Centre in Glasbury and when you reach your destination you telephone us and we collect you!&nbsp;We can also organise instuction and guided sessions for Canoeing, Kayaking or Mountain biking.","url":"\/businesses\/2867"}}];
